1
00:00:35,375 --> 00:00:37,708
[ASAKURA] You want me to
take you to see the nurse?

2
00:00:37,791 --> 00:00:39,000
[KYON]
Hmm...?

3
00:00:41,125 --> 00:00:42,791
[sighs]

4
00:00:42,875 --> 00:00:44,208
Good morning.

5
00:00:44,291 --> 00:00:46,833
I don't think she's
feeling too well.

6
00:00:46,916 --> 00:00:49,791
Take care of her, hm!

7
00:00:51,291 --> 00:00:52,250
[KYON sighs]

8
00:00:53,500 --> 00:00:55,541
[KYON] So why didn't
you come by yesterday?

9
00:00:55,625 --> 00:00:58,208
Thought you wanted to have a
review session or something?

10
00:00:58,291 --> 00:00:59,291
[HARUHI]
Shut up.

11
00:00:59,375 --> 00:01:02,166
I had a review session
by myself, okay?

12
00:01:02,250 --> 00:01:03,458
[KYON]
With a little prodding,

13
00:01:03,541 --> 00:01:05,333
Haruhi told me that
after school yesterday,

14
00:01:05,416 --> 00:01:07,291
she'd gone back and
walked the entire course

15
00:01:07,375 --> 00:01:09,541
we covered on
Saturday by herself.

16
00:01:09,625 --> 00:01:11,041
[HARUHI]
It's hot and I'm tired.

17
00:01:11,125 --> 00:01:13,083
When do we get to
change uniforms?

18
00:01:13,166 --> 00:01:15,291
I wanna change into
my summer uniform now.

19
00:01:15,375 --> 00:01:17,625
Suzumiya, I know I
said this already,

20
00:01:17,708 --> 00:01:19,208
but why don't you just quit

21
00:01:19,291 --> 00:01:21,458
searching for these mysteries
you're never gonna find, okay?

22
00:01:21,541 --> 00:01:22,958
I mean, why don't you
go out and have fun

23
00:01:23,041 --> 00:01:25,125
like a normal high school
student for a change?

24
00:01:25,208 --> 00:01:27,750
What kind of fun does a normal
high school student have?

25
00:01:27,833 --> 00:01:30,458
How 'bout you find a nice guy
and go walking around the city

26
00:01:30,541 --> 00:01:31,916
looking for strange things?

27
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:34,625
It's a date, so you can kill
two birds with one stone.

28
00:01:34,708 --> 00:01:37,125
[HARUHI]
Huh. What do I care about men?

29
00:01:37,208 --> 00:01:40,375
Romantic emotions are
nothing but a passing phase.

30
00:01:40,458 --> 00:01:43,333
Just a form of mental illness.

31
00:01:43,416 --> 00:01:45,500
Heck, every now then,
even I get into the mood for

32
00:01:45,583 --> 00:01:47,166
dumb stuff like that.

33
00:01:47,250 --> 00:01:49,458
I'm a healthy young woman;
I've got needs.

34
00:01:49,541 --> 00:01:52,000
Sometimes I don't know
what to do with myself.

35
00:01:52,083 --> 00:01:54,916
But I'm not stupid enough to
get stuck with all of that grief

36
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:58,208
just because of some momentary
urge to get all mushy.

37
00:01:58,291 --> 00:02:00,958
Besides, if I went out and
really started boy hunting,

38
00:02:01,041 --> 00:02:03,416
what's gonna happen
to the SOS Brigade?

39
00:02:03,500 --> 00:02:05,833
I mean, I just
created the thing.

40
00:02:05,916 --> 00:02:07,666
You could just change the
Brigade into some sort of

41
00:02:07,750 --> 00:02:09,250
random club that has fun

42
00:02:09,333 --> 00:02:10,708
and you'll have a
ton of people in it.

43
00:02:10,791 --> 00:02:12,791
No way! I made the SOS Brigade

44
00:02:12,875 --> 00:02:14,916
because that stuff's
totally boring.

45
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:16,458
I mean, I gotta moe character

46
00:02:16,541 --> 00:02:18,333
and a mysterious
transfer student,

47
00:02:18,416 --> 00:02:20,958
so why hasn't anything
happened yet?!

48
00:02:21,041 --> 00:02:24,916
Oh, why can't a couple of weird
things happen right now?

49
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:27,750
[ASAKURA] Don't go asking
for trouble like that.

50
00:02:27,833 --> 00:02:31,916
But then again, it might
actually be kinda neat

51
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:34,541
if something were to come along
and turn our everyday lives

52
00:02:34,625 --> 00:02:36,583
into something more fun.

53
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:39,208
[sighs]

54
00:02:39,291 --> 00:02:42,375
[KYON] This is a p  never seen Haruhi this down.

55
00:02:42,458 --> 00:02:44,916
Isn't her dejected
little face cute though?

56
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:47,833
I wonder if Miss Suzumiya's
in love or something?

57
00:02:47,916 --> 00:02:49,416
Impossible.

58
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:52,333
[KYON] Okay, Suzumiya falling
in love and, or something weird

59
00:02:52,416 --> 00:02:54,291
popping up to make her
happy are two things

60
00:02:54,375 --> 00:02:57,916
that will definitely not
happen any time soon.

61
00:02:58,000 --> 00:02:59,208
Wrong.

62
00:02:59,291 --> 00:03:01,083
Actually, something weird
was quietly lurking

63
00:03:01,166 --> 00:03:02,833
just around the corner.

64
00:03:14,041 --> 00:03:15,833
[KYON] That morning
as I talked to Haruhi,

65
00:03:15,916 --> 00:03:18,333
I was actually thinking
about something else.

66
00:03:25,041 --> 00:03:27,666
[TEACHER] And now, without
an enemy, Umako Sagano

67
00:03:27,750 --> 00:03:30,083
became tremendously arrogant.

68
00:03:30,166 --> 00:03:32,666
[KYON] Didn't something
like this happen before?

69
00:03:36,875 --> 00:03:38,083
Yo.

70
00:03:44,833 --> 00:03:48,083
[KYON] It was pretty obvious
the handwriting wasn't Nagato's.

71
00:03:48,166 --> 00:03:50,208
Besides, she's not really
the type to go around

72
00:03:50,291 --> 00:03:53,000
putting messages in
a guy's shoe locker.

73
00:03:53,083 --> 00:03:55,208
Could it've been Miss Asahina?

74
00:03:55,291 --> 00:03:58,666
Nah, no way. She'd set
a specific time to meet,

75
00:03:58,750 --> 00:04:00,375
and I doubt she'd
scribble it on paper

76
00:04:00,458 --> 00:04:02,083
torn out of a memo pad.

77
00:04:02,166 --> 00:04:03,375
[door opens]

78
00:04:03,458 --> 00:04:04,833
--[HARUHI] Oh, it's so hot!
--[KYON] Haruhi...

79
00:04:04,916 --> 00:04:07,083
[KYON] Impossible. She'd
just grab me by the collar

80
00:04:07,166 --> 00:04:08,625
and drag me over
to the stairwell

81
00:04:08,708 --> 00:04:10,041
just the like last time.

82
00:04:10,125 --> 00:04:12,083
And Koizumi would just say,
"Hey, let's talk."

83
00:04:12,166 --> 00:04:13,458
[HARUHI sighs]

84
00:04:13,541 --> 00:04:15,583
We definitely need
an air conditioner.

85
00:04:15,666 --> 00:04:17,875
[KYON]
Clearly it's not a love letter.

86
00:04:17,958 --> 00:04:19,833
All I know is, it's
requesting my presence

87
00:04:19,916 --> 00:04:21,458
at a specific location.

88
00:04:21,541 --> 00:04:24,083
Wait a sec... maybe
Tanaguchi and Kunikida

89
00:04:24,166 --> 00:04:25,625
are playing some kinda joke.

90
00:04:25,708 --> 00:04:28,708
Yeah, that's it. That's the
most logical possibility.

91
00:04:28,791 --> 00:04:32,666
Although, I'd expect more
if those two were involved.

92
00:04:32,750 --> 00:04:34,166
Wait! What the heck's that?!

93
00:04:34,250 --> 00:04:35,666
What? They're just pictures.

94
00:04:35,750 --> 00:04:37,625
They're totally cute
shots of Mikuru!

95
00:04:37,708 --> 00:04:38,791
[KYON]
Yeah, I see that!

96
00:04:38,875 --> 00:04:40,208
What the hell're you
doing with these?!

97
00:04:40,291 --> 00:04:43,166
I'm loading them onto the
main page of our website!

98
00:04:43,250 --> 00:04:46,333
Now we'll get tons of email
about cool, weird happenings!

99
00:04:46,416 --> 00:04:48,625
Our site'll get tens
of thousands of hits!

100
00:04:48,708 --> 00:04:51,625
The counter will roll
so high, it'll be nuts!

101
00:04:51,708 --> 00:04:54,375
Wonder if the counter
even goes that high...?

102
00:04:54,458 --> 00:04:55,416
Wait!

103
00:04:55,500 --> 00:04:57,750
Ah! What're you doing,
you idiot?!

104
00:04:57,833 --> 00:04:59,625
I'm putting an end to this.

105
00:04:59,708 --> 00:05:01,875
[KYON] If Miss Asahina found
out that the entire planet

106
00:05:01,958 --> 00:05:04,166
could see pictures of her
wearing that maid outfit--

107
00:05:04,250 --> 00:05:05,958
in stunning poses, I might add--

108
00:05:06,041 --> 00:05:08,125
she would pass out on the spot.

109
00:05:08,208 --> 00:05:10,833
Haruhi glared at me as I
feverishly tried to explain

110
00:05:10,916 --> 00:05:13,083
to her why this was
such a bad thing.

111
00:05:13,166 --> 00:05:15,541
In the end, I don't know if she
understood how dangerous

112
00:05:15,625 --> 00:05:17,875
it was to put such personal
stuff on the internet

113
00:05:17,958 --> 00:05:19,916
where any creep could access it.

114
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:22,125
[HARUHI]
Hmph. Fine, whatever!

115
00:05:22,208 --> 00:05:24,541
[KYON] She reluctantly
agreed to trash them.

116
00:05:24,625 --> 00:05:26,166
Now, this would've been
the time to delete

117
00:05:26,250 --> 00:05:28,125
the photos once and for all,

118
00:05:28,208 --> 00:05:30,875
but it would be a shame
to waste 'em...

119
00:05:34,375 --> 00:05:35,333
[KYON]
There!

120
00:05:36,708 --> 00:05:38,375
That's it. I'm going home.

121
00:05:38,458 --> 00:05:39,541
Huh?

122
00:05:44,541 --> 00:05:45,458
[MIKURU gasps]

123
00:05:45,541 --> 00:05:47,833
Oh, I'm sorry!

124
00:05:47,916 --> 00:05:49,500
Ah...

125
00:05:49,583 --> 00:05:50,833
Uh...

126
00:05:50,916 --> 00:05:52,250
Did something happen?

127
00:05:52,333 --> 00:05:53,958
No, everything's a-okay.

128
00:05:54,041 --> 00:05:57,791
An evil conspiracy's
just been vanquished.

129
00:05:57,875 --> 00:06:00,291
[KYON] Since we had nothing
to do, I was playing Othello

130
00:06:00,375 --> 00:06:02,458
with Miss Asahina when
Koizumi came in

131
00:06:02,541 --> 00:06:03,958
with that smile of his.

132
00:06:04,041 --> 00:06:07,750
Sorry, guys, but I gotta leave
early today to go to work.

133
00:06:07,833 --> 00:06:10,041
[KYON] I wonder what
kind of job he's got?

134
00:06:13,708 --> 00:06:16,041
I'm gonna change,
so don't wait for me.

135
00:06:16,125 --> 00:06:18,333
[KYON] Taking advantage
of Miss Asahina's request,

136
00:06:18,416 --> 00:06:20,291
I bolted from the room.

137
00:06:25,958 --> 00:06:28,541
[KYON] Seeing her standing
there caught me off guard,

138
00:06:28,625 --> 00:06:30,041
to say the least.

139
00:06:33,791 --> 00:06:36,041
Why don't you come in?

140
00:06:36,125 --> 00:06:37,625
It was you...

141
00:06:38,625 --> 00:06:41,333
Yes. Are you surprised?

142
00:06:41,416 --> 00:06:42,833
[KYON]
What d'you want?

143
00:06:42,916 --> 00:06:45,833
I wanted to talk to
you about something.

144
00:06:45,916 --> 00:06:48,916
Actually, it's a question I had.

145
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:51,333
It's about Miss Suzumiya.

146
00:06:51,416 --> 00:06:52,666
What do you think of her?

147
00:06:52,750 --> 00:06:55,375
[KYON] Oh brother, she's
onto Suzumiya as well.

148
00:06:55,458 --> 00:06:58,083
People always say that
it's much better to regret

149
00:06:58,166 --> 00:07:01,375
something you did rather than
regret something you didn't do.

150
00:07:01,458 --> 00:07:04,250
What do you think about that?

151
00:07:04,333 --> 00:07:07,041
Well, I'm not really sure people
always say that, but I think

152
00:07:07,125 --> 00:07:08,583
it means what it means.

153
00:07:08,666 --> 00:07:10,791
Well, then, let's pretend if you
knew that if you kept things

154
00:07:10,875 --> 00:07:12,958
exactly the same as
they are right now,

155
00:07:13,041 --> 00:07:14,666
you'd be completely broke.

156
00:07:14,750 --> 00:07:16,666
And let's say you that just
didn't know how you could

157
00:07:16,750 --> 00:07:18,875
possibly make things any better.

158
00:07:18,958 --> 00:07:20,583
I wonder what you'd
do about that?

159
00:07:20,666 --> 00:07:21,875
I don't understand.

160
00:07:21,958 --> 00:07:23,958
Are you talking about
the Japanese Economy?

161
00:07:24,041 --> 00:07:26,125
As a start, wouldn't you think
about trying to change

162
00:07:26,208 --> 00:07:27,666
something, anything?

163
00:07:27,750 --> 00:07:29,375
I mean, nothing is going
to change if you

164
00:07:29,458 --> 00:07:30,791
stay the same, right?

165
00:07:30,875 --> 00:07:32,875
Well, yeah, I guess if you're
gonna put it that way.

166
00:07:32,958 --> 00:07:35,708
Then you agree with me!

167
00:07:35,791 --> 00:07:38,166
But you know, my superiors
are extremely stubborn

168
00:07:38,250 --> 00:07:40,166
and lack any vision whatsoever.

169
00:07:40,250 --> 00:07:42,458
But you can't have that kind
of thinking out in the field.

170
00:07:42,541 --> 00:07:45,625
If you just twiddle your thumbs,
things'll go from bad to worse.

171
00:07:45,708 --> 00:07:48,125
And if that's the case, wouldn't
it be okay to force change

172
00:07:48,208 --> 00:07:50,625
to happen when you know
it's all for the best?

173
00:07:50,708 --> 00:07:52,083
[KYON]
What's she talking about?

174
00:07:52,166 --> 00:07:53,625
Is there a hidden
camera in here?

175
00:07:53,708 --> 00:07:55,083
Is Tanaguchi hiding
in the closet,

176
00:07:55,166 --> 00:07:56,666
laughing at me right now?

177
00:07:56,750 --> 00:07:58,583
[ASAKURA] I'm getting bored and
just fed up watching something

178
00:07:58,666 --> 00:08:00,708
that doesn't seem to
be changing at all.

179
00:08:00,791 --> 00:08:02,958
That's why I'm going
to kill you and see how

180
00:08:03,041 --> 00:08:04,625
Miss Suzumiya reacts.

181
00:08:04,708 --> 00:08:07,041
[KYON gasps]

182
00:08:09,333 --> 00:08:10,250
[gasps]

183
00:08:10,333 --> 00:08:11,291
[KYON]
What the hell?!

184
00:08:11,375 --> 00:08:12,750
Is she serious?!

185
00:08:12,833 --> 00:08:14,875
Wait, hang on.
What just happened?

186
00:08:14,958 --> 00:08:17,666
Why is Asakura coming
after me with a knife?

187
00:08:17,750 --> 00:08:19,791
Whoa, wait a minute,
what did she just say?

188
00:08:19,875 --> 00:08:20,750
"I'm gonna kill you"?

189
00:08:20,833 --> 00:08:22,291
Naze... why?

190
00:08:22,375 --> 00:08:24,250
Stop kidding around! You're
gonna hurt someone with that!

191
00:08:24,333 --> 00:08:25,333
Even if that's a rubber knife,

192
00:08:25,416 --> 00:08:26,708
you're scaring
the hell outta me!

193
00:08:26,791 --> 00:08:29,541
You think it's a... joke?

194
00:08:29,625 --> 00:08:30,666
Huh...

195
00:08:30,750 --> 00:08:32,166
You don't wanna die?

196
00:08:32,250 --> 00:08:33,708
You don't want me to kill you?

197
00:08:33,791 --> 00:08:36,208
I'm sorry, but I just don't
understand the concept of death

198
00:08:36,291 --> 00:08:37,916
regarding organic lifeforms.

199
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:39,791
Okay, this isn't funny anymore!

200
00:08:39,875 --> 00:08:41,416
I don't know why you're
doing this, but please,

201
00:08:41,500 --> 00:08:42,916
just put the knife down!

202
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:45,125
Heh. I can't.

203
00:08:45,208 --> 00:08:46,833
Because whether you
care about it or not,

204
00:08:46,916 --> 00:08:49,083
I really do want you to die.

205
00:08:52,208 --> 00:08:53,708
[gasps]

206
00:08:53,791 --> 00:08:55,250
[ASAKURA]
It's useless.

207
00:08:55,333 --> 00:08:57,541
Right now, I have the control
over the flow of the data

208
00:08:57,625 --> 00:08:58,916
in this space.

209
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:01,500
Nothing can enter,
nothing can leave.

210
00:09:01,583 --> 00:09:03,458
[KYON] I have no idea
what's going on here.

211
00:09:03,541 --> 00:09:05,166
If anybody understands,
get the hell over here

212
00:09:05,250 --> 00:09:06,500
and explain it to me!

213
00:09:06,583 --> 00:09:08,208
Oh, please, won't
you just give up?

214
00:09:08,291 --> 00:09:11,458
You're gonna die no matter what,
so let me kill you.

215
00:09:11,541 --> 00:09:13,791
[KYON] Just what the
hell are you anyway?

216
00:09:16,416 --> 00:09:17,625
[yells]

217
00:09:22,500 --> 00:09:23,291
Ah-ah...

218
00:09:23,375 --> 00:09:24,958
I already told you it's useless.

219
00:09:25,041 --> 00:09:28,666
Everything in the classroom
is now under my control.

220
00:09:28,750 --> 00:09:29,625
[KYON]
Wait, wait, wait!

221
00:09:29,708 --> 00:09:30,958
What the hell's going on?!

222
00:09:31,041 --> 00:09:33,666
She's gonna kill me to
see how Haruhi reacts?

223
00:09:33,750 --> 00:09:36,083
Haruhi, Haruhi!
Man, she's popular!

224
00:09:36,166 --> 00:09:38,000
And if that's the case,
then why am I the one

225
00:09:38,083 --> 00:09:39,250
that's gotta die?!

226
00:09:39,333 --> 00:09:42,208
Silly me, I shoulda done
this from the get-go.

227
00:09:42,291 --> 00:09:43,416
[gasps]

228
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:45,750
[KYON] I can't move!
Wait, that's not fair!

229
00:09:45,833 --> 00:09:47,375
Your death is the
perfect way to make

230
00:09:47,458 --> 00:09:50,541
Haruhi Suzumiya take some
sort of action, you see?

231
00:09:50,625 --> 00:09:53,916
Finally, I'll be able to observe
a huge explosion of data.

232
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:55,833
It's a once-in-a-lifetime
opportunity!

233
00:09:55,916 --> 00:09:58,583
[KYON]
Tell me about it!

234
00:09:58,666 --> 00:09:59,666
Now you die.

235
00:09:59,750 --> 00:10:00,708
[gasps]

236
00:10:04,750 --> 00:10:06,541
Ow, that hurt!

237
00:10:06,625 --> 00:10:07,500
Wait...

238
00:10:07,583 --> 00:10:08,208
[gasps]

239
00:10:08,291 --> 00:10:10,166
[KYON]
I can move!

240
00:10:12,125 --> 00:10:12,916
Nagato?!

241
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:14,333
[ASAKURA gasps]

242
00:10:17,833 --> 00:10:20,000
[NAGATO]
There are flaws in your program.

243
00:10:20,083 --> 00:10:23,458
Your data shut down and spatial
blockades are faulty.

244
00:10:23,541 --> 00:10:26,916
It is how I detected you,
why I was allowed inside.

245
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:29,708
You stopped me?
But if I kill this human,

246
00:10:29,791 --> 00:10:32,666
Haruhi Suzumiya is bound to
do something interesting.

247
00:10:32,750 --> 00:10:35,708
It's the only way for us
to acquire more information.

