00:20:54,875 --> 00:20:57,291
who saw it fall in love.

494
00:21:00,958 --> 00:21:02,458
It's been ages.

495
00:21:02,541 --> 00:21:04,791
[KYON] In other words, the high
school version of Miss Asahina

496
00:21:04,875 --> 00:21:07,041
is gonna return to her
time in the future.

497
00:21:07,125 --> 00:21:09,125
I wonder when that's
gonna happen...?

498
00:21:09,208 --> 00:21:11,000
And how many years between
the one that's in school

499
00:21:11,083 --> 00:21:12,958
with me and the one I just met?

500
00:21:13,041 --> 00:21:15,541
From the way she looked just
now, it could be three or

501
00:21:15,625 --> 00:21:19,125
even five years. Women change so
drastically when they graduate

502
00:21:19,208 --> 00:21:20,791
from high school.

503
00:21:20,875 --> 00:21:22,958
Better get back
to the classroom.

504
00:21:23,041 --> 00:21:25,291
Man, I'm really hungry.

505
00:21:25,958 --> 00:21:28,625
Hey, you didn't happen to pass
someone in the hall just now

506
00:21:28,708 --> 00:21:30,833
that looked a lot like
Miss Asahina, did you?

507
00:21:30,916 --> 00:21:33,541
[NAGATO] The Mikuru Asahina
from another time plane,

508
00:21:33,625 --> 00:21:35,125
I met her this morning.

509
00:21:35,208 --> 00:21:37,875
I never asked you before, but
can you time travel like her?

510
00:21:37,958 --> 00:21:39,750
Can that data thing
time travel, too?

511
00:21:39,833 --> 00:21:41,291
I am unable to.

512
00:21:41,375 --> 00:21:45,083
However, time travel is not
that difficult to accomplish.

513
00:21:45,166 --> 00:21:47,291
I'd like some tips
on how to do it.

514
00:21:47,375 --> 00:21:49,291
[NAGATO] Language cannot
explain the concept,

515
00:21:49,375 --> 00:21:51,208
nor are you able
to understand it.

516
00:21:51,291 --> 00:21:52,666
Is that so?

517
00:21:52,750 --> 00:21:53,750
[NAGATO]
It is so.

518
00:21:53,833 --> 00:21:55,083
Then I guess it's my loss.

519
00:21:55,166 --> 00:21:56,833
[NAGATO]
Your loss.

520
00:21:56,916 --> 00:21:59,541
Nagato, thanks again
for yesterday.

521
00:21:59,625 --> 00:22:02,541
Don't thank me. Asakura's
abnormal behavior

522
00:22:02,625 --> 00:22:06,041
was my responsibility. I failed.

523
00:22:06,125 --> 00:22:09,125
I really think you look
better without glasses.

524
00:22:14,125 --> 00:22:15,000
[HARUHI]
Where were you?!

525
00:22:15,083 --> 00:22:16,166
I'd thought you'd be back!

526
00:22:16,250 --> 00:22:18,000
I was waiting, and
didn't even eat lunch!

527
00:22:18,083 --> 00:22:20,125
[KYON] Could you say that again,
but like you're an old friend

528
00:22:20,208 --> 00:22:21,958
who's embarrassed and
only acting angry?

529
00:22:22,041 --> 00:22:24,416
[HARUHI] Stop being an idiot
and come with me right now!

530
00:22:24,500 --> 00:22:26,541
I went to the teacher's
lounge and asked Okabe.

531
00:22:26,625 --> 00:22:28,416
Get this: no one
knew that Asakura

532
00:22:28,500 --> 00:22:30,208
was transferring
until this morning.

533
00:22:30,291 --> 00:22:32,500
Apparently, someone claiming
to be her father called in

534
00:22:32,583 --> 00:22:34,625
and said they were moving away!
Just like that!

535
00:22:34,708 --> 00:22:37,083
You wanna know where
they're moving to? Canada!

536
00:22:37,166 --> 00:22:39,625
Can you believe that?!
Something's fishy here.

537
00:22:39,708 --> 00:22:41,041
[KYON]
Ya think?

538
00:22:41,125 --> 00:22:42,791
[HARUHI] There's more!
I asked for their contact info

539
00:22:42,875 --> 00:22:44,541
in Canada. You know
what they told me?

540
00:22:44,625 --> 00:22:46,708
"Sorry, we don't have
that information."

541
00:22:46,791 --> 00:22:49,208
At the very least, you tell
someone your new address!

542
00:22:49,291 --> 00:22:51,000
I'm sure something
funny's going on!

543
00:22:51,083 --> 00:22:52,041
[KYON]
No, there isn't.

544
00:22:52,125 --> 00:22:53,208
[HARUHI]
I kept up my interrogations

545
00:22:53,291 --> 00:22:55,250
until I got Asakura's
old address.

546
00:22:55,333 --> 00:22:57,166
After school, I'm going
straight over there.

547
00:22:57,250 --> 00:22:59,583
I'll crack this thing wide open!

548
00:23:00,750 --> 00:23:03,708
[KYON] Still the same.
She never listens to anything.

549
00:23:03,791 --> 00:23:06,125
And I won't stop her.
Hey, Haruhi's the one

550
00:23:06,208 --> 00:23:07,875
who's wasting her time
with this, not me.

551
00:23:07,958 --> 00:23:09,166
[HARUHI]
And you're coming, too.

552
00:23:09,250 --> 00:23:10,083
Why me?!

553
00:23:10,166 --> 00:23:10,750
[KYON grunts]

554
00:23:10,833 --> 00:23:12,708
Ow!

555
00:23:12,791 --> 00:23:16,458
And you call yourself a member
of the SOS Brigade?!

